Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%grams} for ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the
mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Cook so there's
> no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Drain the fat from the beef. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @Coleslaw Mix{120%grams} and @Sugar Snap Peas{80%grams} to the beef. Fry
for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @Ginger Puree{15%grams} and garlic. Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Hoisin Sauce{64%grams}, @Soy Sauce{25%milliliter} and
@Water{50%milliliter}.

Bring to the boil and simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @Udon Noodles{220%grams} to the pan. Toss to coat, using a #fork{} to
gently separate them. Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season if needed. Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Share the noodles between your bowls. Enjoy!